The paper deals with algorithmic and structural aspects of connectivity in hypergraphs, which is a topic in both theoretical computer science and discrete mathematics. The use of vertex ordering and sparsification techniques suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), while the approximation algorithm and hypercactus representation suggest a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA), respectively. The paper also involves graph theory (cs.DM) and complexity theory (cs.CC) in the analysis of the algorithms.
